FBIS4-65901 "drweu101_q_94004" FBIS-WEU-94-101 Daily Report 24 May 1994 TURKEY Security Forces Continue Operations in Southeast Security Forces Continue Operations in Southeast 7 Civilians Die in Siirt TA2405144694 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1430 GMT 24 May 94 TA2405144694 Ankara ANATOLIA English BFN [Text] Baykan, May 24 (A.A) -- Terrorists who raided Ardicli village of Baykan District in southeastern Siirt Province, killed seven people including three children, and wounded another five, it was reported on Tuesday [24 May]. They escaped after the attack when security forces arrived on the scene of the raid. Officials said that operations were started to catch the terrorists.
